  "plan": "1) Update /app/run_stream_analysis_fix.py to handle mismatched token counts robustly:\n   - After splitting a data line into parts, produce vals = parts[1:]\n   - If len(vals) != len(barcodes):\n       - If len(vals) > len(barcodes): keep the last len(barcodes) tokens (assume an extra leading token)\n       - If len(vals) < len(barcodes): left-pad with zeros to match barcodes (rare but safe)\n   - Strip surrounding quotes from each numeric token before int conversion.\n2) Re-run the updated script with the venv Python.\n3) Print lr_results.csv, /app/trace.md head, and /app/answer.txt to verify outputs.\n\nI expect this to produce non-zero cells unless the selected genes truly have zero counts. The updated parser will be more robust to slight formatting differences across samples.",
  "commands": [
